&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3 i.e. &amp;#39;error lies in part 3 of the sentence.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In part C of the sentence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;the usage of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;an&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is incorrect Instead, use&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;the&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;According to rule,&lt;/strong&gt; use the definite article with&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;geographical features&lt;/strong&gt;, such as &lt;em&gt;mountain ranges, groups of islands, rivers, seas, oceans, and canals.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
For example- the Himalayas, The Arctic Ocean, The St. Lawrence River, The Suez Canal, etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So the correct sentence is:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;em&gt;All one&amp;#39;s endless longing for life&amp;#39;s pleasures is stilled on the shores of&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;the Arabian Sea.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;driven her into the&amp;nbsp;forest&amp;nbsp;full of insurgents&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;driven her into a forest&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;should be there in place of&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;driven her into the forest&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;The use of the article A&amp;#39; is correct because it&amp;#39;s a singular, countable noun used for the first time.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When &amp;#39;forest&amp;#39; is referred the second time, the article &amp;#39;the&amp;#39; is used as it becomes specific.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct sentence is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Whatever she found at the Peak had driven her into &lt;strong&gt;a&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;forest&amp;nbsp;full of insurgents despite her injury and her lack of familiarity with the&amp;nbsp;forest&amp;nbsp;or the world outside hers.&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The error lies in part B; Place article &amp;#39;the&amp;#39; before Time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Article &amp;quot;the&amp;quot; is used before the followings nouns-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;background-color: (255, 255, 255); width: 500px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot; wfd-id=&quot;4336&quot;&gt;Nouns&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot; wfd-id=&quot;4335&quot;&gt;Examples&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;heavenly bodies&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;the sun, the stars&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;water bodies&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;the pacific ocean&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;mountain ranges&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;the Himalayas&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;superlative degree before a noun&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;the best product&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Invention&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;the television&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Dynasties and Empires&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;the Gupta dynasty&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Newspaper and magazines&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;The Gaurdian, The TOI&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Holy books&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;The bible, the Vedas&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&amp;quot;Title&amp;quot; honored&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;Gandhi the Mahatama&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As per the table explained above, article &amp;#39;the&amp;quot; will be used before &amp;#39;time because it is a &amp;#39;magazine&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct Sentence-&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;Who do you think &lt;strong&gt;the &lt;/strong&gt;Time will feature person of the year for 2020?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-3f24567e-7fff-a70b-8d8e-8646326c8549&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Articles&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;are words that define a noun as specific or unspecific.&amp;nbsp;There are some rules regarding the use of articles given below:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/428.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 35px; height: 35px; float: left;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Indefinite articles-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;a, an.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Definite articles-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;the.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The definite article &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is used with the name of things that are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;unique or already mentioned before.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Whereas the article&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;a&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is used&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;with the name of things that are&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;not specific&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;For example:&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​I met&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;a person&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;on my way to the office.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The person&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;turned out to be an old friend.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence according to the rules given above,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;a&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be the most appropriate choice for the 1st blank as&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;not much is known about the given noun&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Since the drawing-room is already a part of the house,&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;the&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;will be the most appropriate choice for the &lt;strong&gt;2nd&amp;nbsp;blank&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct Sentence&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;A&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;new carpet was laid out in &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;the&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;drawing-room today.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 4) i.e no article.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-3f24567e-7fff-a70b-8d8e-8646326c8549&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/clipboard.png&quot; style=&quot;font-weight: 700; width: 30px; height: 30px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Articles&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;are words that define a noun as &lt;strong&gt;specific or unspecific.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Indefinite articles-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;a, an.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Definite articles-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;the.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The definite article &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;the&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is used with the name of things that are&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;unique or already mentioned before.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;The&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;isn&amp;#39;t used with the&lt;strong&gt; name of a language &lt;/strong&gt;though it can be used before&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;nationality&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For example:
	&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​&lt;strong&gt;The Spanish&lt;/strong&gt; were very hospitable. (People)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;I like speaking &lt;strong&gt;French.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;(Language)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence according to the rule given above,&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;no article&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;will be the most appropriate choice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct Sentence&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;I studied &lt;strong&gt;French&lt;/strong&gt; in high school for four years.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; &lt;u style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;O&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;&quot;&gt;ption 1)&lt;/u&gt; i.e. &lt;u&gt;A&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-ff1db11e-7fff-7f29-210f-dce40e0be8d8&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/09/clipboard.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 44px; height: 44px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:16px;&quot;&gt;Explanation:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​If &lt;strong&gt;nouns &lt;/strong&gt;are followed by the preposition&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;of&amp;#39;,&lt;/strong&gt; an &lt;strong&gt;article &lt;/strong&gt;will precede the noun.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Example:
	&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;I saw&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;bunch of &lt;/strong&gt;crooks yesterday.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/false%20%282%29.png&quot; style=&quot;font-weight: 700; white-space: pre-wrap; width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;I saw &lt;strong&gt;a bunch of&lt;/strong&gt; crooks yesterday&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;.&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/right%20%281%29.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 25px; height: 25px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;As per the rule and example given above,&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;The milk cake&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be used&amp;nbsp;instead of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Milk cake&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;1st&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;part&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The article &amp;#39;the&amp;#39; is used because the milk cake of a specific place is being talked about.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct Sentence&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;The milk cake of Alwar&lt;/strong&gt; is known for its superior quality and authenticity.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/21/09/5f730be8ffb6c8124eeabfde_16321378771981.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 240px; height: 37px; float: left;&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;&quot; /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;The&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is often used before the&lt;strong&gt; superlative degree.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Example:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;This is&lt;strong&gt; the best &lt;/strong&gt;car in our town.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the correct answer is:&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&amp;nbsp;the, a&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The above&lt;strong&gt; question &lt;/strong&gt;is to&lt;strong&gt; fill in the blanks with articles.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There are&lt;strong&gt; three articles&lt;/strong&gt; in&lt;strong&gt; English.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s&lt;strong&gt; consider&lt;/strong&gt; the&lt;strong&gt; usage&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;of&lt;/strong&gt; the articles&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;the&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;and &amp;#39;a&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The&amp;nbsp; is used to express:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The unique things&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The celestial bodies&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The names of rivers, mountains, deserts, plateaus etc.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The names of books, magazines, newspapers etc.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;the further qualified nouns&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The noun already discussed.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;the superlative degree&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;the cardinal numbers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A is used to denote :&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Common nouns beginning with consonants&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Common singular things.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In&lt;/strong&gt; the &lt;strong&gt;above sentence,&lt;/strong&gt; the&lt;strong&gt; wedding pictures&lt;/strong&gt; is a &lt;strong&gt;unique&lt;/strong&gt; thing, so &amp;#39;the&amp;#39; will be used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; twelve-hour slide show&lt;/strong&gt; is a &lt;strong&gt;common singular noun,&lt;/strong&gt; so&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;A&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;will be&lt;strong&gt; used.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The complete sentence is&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;When Lulu asked to see the&amp;nbsp;wedding pictures, she didn&amp;rsquo;t expect Annie to put on a&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;twelve-hour slide show&amp;quot;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1) i.e A, the, the&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-3f24567e-7fff-a70b-8d8e-8646326c8549&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Articles&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;are words that define a noun as specific or unspecific.&amp;nbsp;There are some rules regarding the use of articles given below:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/428.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 35px; height: 35px; float: left;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Indefinite articles-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;a, an.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Definite articles-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;the.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The definite article &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;the&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is used with the name of things that are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;unique or already mentioned before.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Whereas the article&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;a&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is used&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;with the name of things that are&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;not specific&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The article&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;an&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is used with the words&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;having 1st letter as a vowel and&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt; having the sound of a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;vowel.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;For example:&lt;/em&gt;
	&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​I met&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;a person&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;on my way to the office.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The person&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;turned out to be an old friend.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;In the 1st blank, the article &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;a&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be correct as an &lt;strong&gt;unspecified event&lt;/strong&gt; of &amp;#39;super moon&amp;#39; has been mentioned here.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;In the 2nd&amp;nbsp;blank, the article&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;the&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be correct as &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;moon&amp;#39; is a celestial body.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;In the 3rd&amp;nbsp;blank, the article&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;the&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;will be correct as &lt;b&gt;the event mentioned here has already been talked about earlier.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence according to the rules given above,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;1st option&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;will be the most appropriate choice for the given&amp;nbsp;blanks.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct Sentence&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;A&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;super moon occurs when &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;the&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; moon&amp;rsquo;s orbit is at its closest to Earth and at &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;the&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; same time it is full.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is option 3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sometimes an article modifies a noun that is also modified by an adjective. The usual word order is article + adjective + noun. If the article is indefinite, choose &amp;#39;a&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;or &amp;#39;an&amp;#39; based on the word that immediately follows it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct sentence is: Kiran will bring a small gift to Chandu&amp;rsquo;s party.&lt;/p&gt;
